@node SE_Introduction    "ShapeGenerator/Introduction"
@prev main
@next SE_Requirements

                    @{b}Introduction@{ub}

     I was working on one of my projects and i thought: "How can i create
     a BB2 shapes file without writing a lot of lines all the times?".
     So i spent some hours to write this simple program. OK, not so good
     its interface, but it is very easy to use and it works fine! 
     It simply load some iff brushes and join them saving the result in
     a BB2 shapes file.

     This program has been developed using BlitzBasic2 by Acid Software.

     See the @{" Usage " link SE_Usage} chapter about its usage.


@endnode

